I'm Mandi Solone,
a full stack web developer.

About Me

Welcome to my corner of the web! I'm Mandi Solone, a budding full stack web developer passionate about crafting functional and beautiful digital experiences. Beyond coding, I cherish family time and enjoy adventures with my four-legged friends. When not at the computer, I recharge at the beach or express my creativity through photography. With skills ranging from front-end development to back-end, I'm dedicated to continuous learning and growth. Explore my work and feel free to reach out – I'm thrilled to share my journey in web development with you!

My Projects

This Website

This project aims to create a clean, responsive website page using HTML and CSS. Key features include a responsive design, navigation menu, CSS styling, multimedia integration, and cross-browser compatibility. Includes HTML and CSS files, and image assets.

Mondrian Artwork Recreation Using CSS Grid

This project aimed to recreate Piet Mondrian's iconic artwork using CSS Grid, capturing his distinctive style of geometric shapes and primary colors. CSS Grid facilitated precise layout and alignment of elements, including vertical and horizontal lines, rectangles, and color blocks.

JavaScript Games

This project centered around developing JavaScript games. It featured a random dice roll game that declares the winner and a music game playable via clicking or keyboard input for sound activation.


My Skills

Analytical & Strategic Thinking:

I excel in analyzing data and developing strategic plans to achieve targets, skills that are essential for solving complex problems in software engineering.

Problem Solving:

My experience in sales management has honed my ability to tackle challenges head-on and find innovative solutions, which translates seamlessly to the world of software development.

Proficiency in Productivity Tools:

I am proficient in various productivity tools such as Salesforce, Gmail, Google Docs, and MS Office, demonstrating my adaptability to different software platforms and my ease with technology.

Leadership & Coaching:

As a director and manager, I have honed my leadership and coaching skills, empowering teams to achieve their goals. These skills are invaluable for fostering collaboration and driving success in software engineering projects.

Time Management & Efficiency:

I am skilled in managing my time efficiently to meet deadlines and deliver results. This ability to prioritize tasks and optimize resources is crucial in the fast-paced environment of software development.
